This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes an extension of the DAgger algorithm for imitation learning. The paper also uses image frames from a front-facing camera as sensory input, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with autonomous driving, which is a common application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper proposes a query-efficient algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
